# Why these 4 make your project "Microservice Ready"
BCrypt: Ensures you are following industry security standards (OWASP).

Global Exception Handling: Makes your API "user-friendly" for the frontend developer.

JWT Claims: This is the "secret sauce" for microservices. It allows your Case Handling Service to know who the user is without ever talking to the Auth Service database.

Logout Audit: Completes the "Life Cycle" of a session for compliance.


## 2. RBAC - Role-Based Access Control (The "Key" Check)

1. JWT Token Validation (The "ID Card" Check)



Add BCrypt: Update AuthService to hash passwords during signup and check them during login.

Enhance JWT Claims: Update your JwtUtil to include roles and userId in the payload.

Add Global Exception Handling: Create a @RestControllerAdvice class so that "User Not Found" returns a clean 404 instead of a crash.
